description:
Shattershot Part 2 - The Masters of Inevitability

The X-men Gold Strike Force protects the rebel Arize (suffering from amnesia) from a direct attack by soldiers of the pirate network from Mojoverse at the X-mansion. After the troops are defeated Arize (whose memory has been restored by one of the soldiers) leaves on his own.

Angel of Death

While attempting to single handedly hold off a terrorist attack, Archangel is badly injured. He see a vision of Amalgam "the Angel of Death" and flashbacks back to the Mutant Massacre in the Morlock tunnels when he first saw the vision.

The Roots of the Past

Bishop speaks to Storm about the circumstances surrounding his arrival among the X-men and difficulty assimilating.

Pin-ups: Colossus/Strong Guy, Storm/Cannonball, Colossus/Brood, Archangel
name: Shattershot Part 2: The Masters of Inevitability

description:
Sabretooths presence at the Institute sets off a chain reaction which results in Jubilees kidnapping. Shadowcat dives into the Morlock Tunnels to save her fellow X-girl. Which Morlock has laid stake in Jubilee? And will Kitty Pryde be able to tackle this mission on her own?

On the hunt for Jubilee, the X-Men must depend on Sabretooth, who'd gladly kill them all in a second.

"Trust is a Two-Edged Sword"

Caliban abducts Jubilee and demands an exchange of her life for that of Sabretooth's, a guest in the X-Mansion. Xavier allows Kitty Pryde to take Sabretooth to parlay. The two scuffle in the sewers and then run into a monster in one of the alleys. Caliban rushes in to help. Sabretooth sees Caliban getting worked over and uses a trick of Kitty's to free himself from his manacles. Sabretooth dispatches the monster and then marks Caliban (as payback for breaking Sabretooth's back). Kitty and Jubilee subdue Sabretooth and get him back to the mansion.

"And Nothing Will Ever Be the Same"

Bishop runs through a Danger Room scenario dealing with a past mission with the XSE. Upon completion, he decides to take a walk with Jubilee.

Notes: This annual contains two pin-ups, one of Wolverine and one of the next Cable story arc. It also has an unfinished Uncanny X-Men cover by John Romita, Jr., as well as a pencilled story page from the first story.
name: Trust is a Two-Edged Sword/And Nothing Will Ever be the Same

description: In Part 2 of New Blood, the public and the press are up in arms over a series of brutal murders. A mysterious man known as Brick goes after the heads of all the crime families in Star City. Can Ollie and Connor take out this new kingpin of crime?
name: New Blood Part Two: Fronting

description: Green Arrow, Batgirl, Robin and Spoiler race to rescue Eddie Fyers who is being quite literally crucified by Agrippina and the soldiers of the Ninth Legion. She is searching for the legendary relic, the eagle of the ninth, and believes Jack Drake knows where it is. Eddie (who is posing as drake) is rescued, and Agrippina possibly perishes when her building is destroyed by fire. Later, Jack reveals to his son that the eagle is indeed in his possession.
name: Morituri

description: Helping Batman out, Batgirl learns that he is after someone named Alpha. Nobody seems to know who Alpha is, apart from Cain. So, disguised as a reporter, Batgirl goes in to Blackgate Penitentiary to talk to Cain, her father, but finds that she must deal with her anger towards him rather than ask the questions she needs to. She does, however, find out that her birthday is the 26th of January.
name: Father's Day

description: Batgirl wants to help Batman solve a murder, but he tells her she's not ready to be a detective. They are able to track down the criminal group responsible and pin-point the one who pulled the trigger, but Batgirl feels that isn't enough. Now, Batman says, she's ready to be a detective.
name: Lesson One

description: Batgirl pursues the Alpha by beating up mobs all over Gotham. During one session she finds a man who does not know his own identity. She takes him to an arms shipment at the docks and finds out this man is the one they have been searching for.
name: Blank Slate

description: Both Batman and Batgirl have discovered that Alpha has brought a cold fusion bomb to Gotham City, and Batgirl must work with the amnesiac Alpha to discover and disable it. They find it on the city limits, but as they do, Alpha remembers who he is. However, Batgirl reveals to him that she is the girl raised by Alpha's mentor Cain, proving that people can change, and Alpha deactivates the bomb and takes up a life as Michael Sommers once more.
name: Point blank!

description:
While rescuing a girl from an abductor that turns out to be her father (and indeed the one person the girl wants to be with), Batgirl realize that David Cain really is her father.

David Cain returns to Blackgate Penitentiary after giving Cassandra a gift. Upon opening it Cass discovers it's a small assassin knife. She takes it to Barbara Gordon and Batman, who both agree it's a nice knife but have no idea why Cain gave it to her. While with Barbara a call comes in about a kidnapping.

Jill is a little girl who is also a talented artist, and she has been abducted by David Sullivan. Her mother is her agent and cares more about the gallery opening then her daughter well being. Batgirl notes this and waits outside till David shows up.

When he does Batgirl follows him home where Jill is being kept. She confronts him but David and Jill make an escape via a hang glider and some insane stunts. Even with these Batgirl is able to catch them but when she tries to rescue Jill, Jill doesn't want to leave David's side.

That is when Batgirl realizes that David is Jill's father and that Cain is her father. David pleads to let him and Jill disappear but Batgirl can't do that and lets David get captured. Jill is returned to her unloving mother and Cass returns home to break the knife that her father gave to her.
name: Thicker than Water

description:
By special guest team Jeff Parker (ROBIN, The Interman) and newcomer Andersen Gabrych! Batman has forbidden Batgirl from going on missions with Spoiler. So what's a girl to do when her best friend shows up ready for action? The results of their escapades will have huge repercussions on both characters' lives!

Batman tells Batgirl she can no longer hang out with Spoiler, as the young girl is not ready to be a heroine. When Spoiler comes over to see her, Batgirl disregards this and they head out around Gotham until they spot a potential gang fight. Batgirl tells Spoiler to stay out of it, and when she doesn't, she comes to the decision that Batman was right about her.
name: Testline

description:
Overview

First issue by award-winning new regular writer Dylan Horrocks (HUNTER: THE AGE OF MAGIC, Hicksville)! Also making their BATGIRL debut are Planet of the Apes artist Adrian Sibar and SUPERMAN inker Andy Owens! A mysterious metahuman called Black Wind has turned Batgirl's world upside down. Not only is he more than a match for Batgirl on the battlefield, but he also seems to have swept her off her proverbial feet. The only solution, as Babs sees it, is a cruise. But when Black Wind and another familiar metahuman show up on the same ship, Cassandra's vacation takes a turn for the worse!

Spoilers

Batgirl encounters the Black Wind, leader of a rebel group from Tarakstan, in Gotham. When Oracle persuades Batman that Batgirl really needs a break away from Gotham, the two ladies go on a cruise. Oddly enough, they soon discover that Superboy is aboard the boat, as is Vilom Namali, a Taraksanian businessman assumed to have been Black Wind's target in Gotham.
name: Black Wind

description:
Overview

New writer Dylan Horrocks continues his run on BATGIRL! Babs thought taking Cassandra on an ocean cruise would be the perfect diversion from crime-fighting. Boy, was she wrong! Not only is the mysterious metahuman known as Black Wind onboard, but so is a dirty businessman and his mammoth bodyguard, Ludo. Plus, a guest appearance by Superboy!

Spoilers

Somewhat inevitably, Batgirl encounters Black Wind aboard their cruise ship, and there is soon a confrontation, with Black Wind and his supporters claiming they are to bring justice to Vilom Namali, an unscrupulous Tarakstani oil magante who once destroyed a village in the name of oil. A confusing confrontation ensues when Superboy gets involved, and after Black Wind is captured, Batgirl wants to go home. She and Superboy also express an attraction to one another; on Batgirl's side, this is partly the result of an uncomfortability with an undeniable chemistry between her and Black Wind.
name: Little Bat

description: When she hears that Black Wind has escaped custody, and probably left the country, Batgirl heads to Smallville to track down Superboy, in search of romance. They are interrupted by various things, such as Ma Kent and an plane, before encountering a being escaped from S.T.A.R. Labs which seems aggressive, but which Batgirl can tell is simply lonely. By the end of this encounter, the two realize that they don't really want to do the romance thing, but they do want to remain friends.
name: Body Language

description: Batman and Batgirl track down Doctor Death, who is supplying a deadly poison to the Russian mafia in Gotham and auctioning it off to other foreign interests, including a bidder from Tarakstan. In the midst of the investigation, Batman finds out about Batgirl's recent visit to Kansas and warns her not to spend any more time with Superboy.
name: Death in a Bottle

description: Under the cover of an investigative mission for Wayne Enterprises, Batman and Batgirl arrive in Tarakstan to track down Doctor Death, whom they believe has been supplying a group of terrorists (or freedom fighters...) with a deadly poison. Here they encounter Black Wind, the leader of the Sakuri Lions group, but discover that he knows nothing of any such thing. However, their supposed guide, academic Jira Vidorja, knows exactly what's going on.
name: Seeds of Blood

description: Batman and Batgirl discover that the Sakuri Lions are not the ones who have purchased the poison from Doctor Death - it is the Tarakstanian government who are testing it on innocent citizens and wish to use it against the Sakuri Lions. An excellent source of oil. The heroes accompany the Lions to the place where the poison is being tested and capture Doctor Death. When the poison is released, Black Wind tries to contain it. He succeeds, but dies in the attempt, much to Batgirl's horror. She and Batman leave the country, horrified at its rulers, with Bruce Wayne telling them he will never invest a single dollar in their nation.
name: Harvest of Death

description: Oracle tells Batgirl as her time in the costume, about how much she enjoyed it, including the attention it got her from the men. While gradually getting hints of a dangerous new designer drug called Soul on the streets of Gotham, Batgirl wears Oracle's old costume and finds that although it is very different, she doesn't want to wear it again.
name: Soul

description: Batgirl discovers that an all-girl meta-human street gang called The Lost Girls is supplying the designer drug Soul on Gotham's streets. It seems that Soul has different effects on different people - good people enter a beatific trance, while bad people become dangerously enraged. Batgirl soon finds herself in trouble with the gang and when Oracle finds that everyone else is unavailable, she reluctantly has to send in Nightwing, whom she recently split up with, to rescue Batgirl. However, Batgirl has picked up on the fact that Oracle is hurt about the end of this relationship and when Nightwing appears on the scene, she throws him out of the window (thankfully on the ground floor), no longer needing a rescue.
name: The Lost Girls

description:
Overview

The Doll Man lurks beneath the streets of Gotham City, abducting debutantes and models and remaking them to satisfy his own twisted needs. Can Batgirl find this psychopath before he strikes again?
name: The Doll's House

description: Batgirl investigates some kidnappings which indicate a possible slave trade, despite being ordered by Batman to come back to the Clock Tower. She catches up with the kidnappees, but in doing so she interrupts an investigation Batman and Robin had been carrying it out, setting the end of the kidnapping ring back several months. Batman tells her he has no choice, but to retire her as Batgirl.
name: Human Resources

description: Cassandra Cain is no longer Batgirl, for Batman will not allow her to continue in the role. Oracle is upset, because he didn't tell Batgirl how proud of her he is. Cassandra takes off with one of Oracle's old costumes, and pitches in with the efforts to help calm the riots caused by the drug Soul. She sees some women snatch some corpses, and following them she comes across Doctor Death and the Lost Girls. And before long, Batman has caught up with them as well, and is not at all pleased.
name: Down Among the Dead Men

description:
Overview

A fantastic extra-sized 50th issue featuring the fracas between Batgirl and Batman! For months, Batgirl's feelings of resentment toward Batman have risen from simmer to boil. Now, fueled by the emotion-charging drug Soul, Batgirl explodes in a fury of fists and feet. That's right: It's Batgirl vs. Batman - the knockdown, drag-out battle you thought you'd never see!

Spoilers



Batgirl and Batman confront one another in a cemetery, and just to make things interesting, the mad scientist Doctor Death exposes them to the drug Soul in a concentrated form. They fight one another across the city, with Robin and Nightwing in pursuit, Oracle watching from the tower. Robin manages to trick Doctor Death into yielding an antidote to Soul, and Batman/Batgirl's fight and chase ends in a plunge from a bridge, after which the two of them simply embrace, something Cain never allowed. Batgirl says her loyalty will always be to the bat and what it means, and Batman welcomes her back into the fold.
name: Tough Love

description: In their search for the reasons behind their visitations by the long-dead spirits of their past, Jesse and Damage are joined by the other Titans, only to discover an imposing complex under the desert. And within it, the true source of the ghosts that haunt the desert above.
name: Ghost Dance Part Two

description: Things start to fall apart for the Titans. After saving a far-off universe, the Titans settle down to deal with the problems around them and among them. If getting by in a demolished headquarters wasn't bad enough, then there's the disintegration of the marital relationship of Tempest and Dolphin to consider. But what about that blip on the radar screen...signaling the return of a founding Titans member?
name: Broken

description: Starfire makes her dramatic reappearance on the American super-heroic scene...by going on a rampage in a vain attempt to destroy every satellite dish in America. The Titans have no choice but to stop her. But what happens to America if they succeed?
name: Murder By Consensus Part One

description: "Murder By Consensus," Part 2 of 3! The Consensus is coming to Earth, slipping into the world's consciousness via radio and television signals. Starfire has returned to stop it, but what chance does she have when half the Titans are already infected? Continued in next month's issue #50!
name: Murder By Consensus Part Two

description:
Climactic final issue! If Earth is to survive, the Titans must destroy the Consensus and the alien creature that gives the Consensus its collective opinion. But it won't be easy, since the entirety of a brainwashed humanity doesn't share the Titans' point of view!

The world seems to be happy, everyone agrees that the Consensus is a good thing, so they are not pleased when the female Titans attack the alien landing ship. When the other Titans follow them inside, they regain control of their minds, and discover the truth: a dead alien's lies are being broadcast through the vessel, and the army of the Consensus is the human race - once the whole world has been won over, it will make everyone attack one another... or worse. They are able to project this truth to the crowds outside, who are saddened to know that this peaceful future is nothing but a delusion.
name: Murder By Consensus Conclusion

description: Both Robin and Impulse are now back with Young Justice and the team decide to invade Zandia to take revenge on Baron Agua Sin Gaaz for the death of Empress father. Snapper Carr assists them with details of Zandia and while Secret has a confrontation with Sin Gaaz on the mental plane, Wonder Girl calls in an army of young heroes to help them. In Zandia the Baron tells Devastation of the heros likely impending arrival and she is excited to have another chance to kill Wonder Girl.
name: Fighting Maad, Part Three: A.W.O.L.

description: Young Justice and friends head to Zandia to take on Sin Gaaz and Lady Zand once and for all!
name: Fighting Maad, Part Four: MUBAR (Messed Up Beyond All Recognition)

description: The final showdown between Empress and Lady Zand and they've both brought a lot of friends along to help!
name: Zand on the Run

description: Young Justice gets their own reality show. Secret visits her father in prison and Empress learns that taking care of babies isn't easy, especially when the babies in question are really your parents!
name: The Unreal World

description:
Overview

It's Secret vs. Young Justice! Amid feelings of betrayal, the team's most innocent member turns to the dark side. Unfortunately, the rest of the team isn't powerful enough to contain her!
name: Dead Man Sprinting

description: Darkseid sets his sights on Secret and this time? She's more than willing to join up with him.
name: Break on Through to the Other Seid

description: Young Justice says goodbye to two of their members as the conflict between Secret and the rest of the team reaches a head.
name: I've Got a Secret

description: Superboy's one millionth clone, the Toy Robin and the personification of the Speed Force meet to investigate a mystery. A member of the ancient Young Justice team is seemingly still alive inside a delicate suspension tube. Who is it...?
name: Just Ice, Cubed

description: Race through the streets of London gangster-style in this new 3-issue miniseries! When camera-girl Rosi Blades films Zen gangster Tony Ling chasing down a runaway gang member, she quickly finds herself caught in a mad duel over a stolen case.
name: Two-Step Part 1

description: Part 2 of the action-packed new miniseries by Warren Ellis! In this issue, the Quarry gang is ready to kill whoever took the case that contains Boss Quarry's most prized possession. They hire the services of Filthy Ron to go after Zenboy and Camgirl. Can they survive his attack? Will Camgirl meet her hit quota this month? And what is Filthy Ron doing to that two-door sedan?
name: Two-Step Part 2

description: The chase continues as Rosi and Tony flee Filthy Ron! Tony decides to deal with the Quarrys and get them off their backs. It's the climactic fight scene featuring all out sedan- shagging action that cannot be missed. Could this all really be a love story?
name: Two-Step Part 3

description: Astronaut John Jameson crash-lands on a planet circling the other side of the sun, a near duplicate of our world called Counter-Earth! There, a strange society exists ruled by the High Evolutionary! Served by an army of bizarre Beastials and the relentless Machine Men, the master of genetics rules with an iron grip. A spaceship has been sent to rescue the stranded astronaut, and hitching a ride is Spider-Man! Unfortunately, also onboard are two of the web-slinger's most malicious adversaries: Venom and Carnage! Soon Spidey and the gruesome twosome will all arrive on the strange new world, and then the fun will really begin!

In search of astronaut John Jameson, Spider-Man has ridden a spaceship to the alien world called Counter Earth, and along for the ride are the sinister symbiotes known as Venom and Carnage! But before the web-slinger can tackle the terrible twosome, he's surrounded by the agents of the High Evolutionary, the menacing Machine Men! And just when it looks like things couldn't get any worse, the Counter Earth version of the Green Goblin appears!

Continuing the all-new adventures (not adaptations) set in the continuity of the new Fox Kids cartoon! Something big, grotesque and unbelievably strong stalks the streets of Counter-Earth's Manhattan... something that's hunting a certain off-world web-spinner! But the Brute has a tragic secret that will shock Spider-Man... that is, if he survives!
name: Enter The Brute!

description: On this strange world called Counter-Earth, what lies beyond the dystopian Manhattan landscape? Our off-world wall-crawler finds himself in the place called Harmony, a land so filled with wonder and enchantment, it calls to mind Asgard itself. But danger abounds here too, and the High Evolutionary still wants Spider-Man dead! But can the web-spinner flee Harmony when he thinks he just spotted the girl once known as Gwen Stacy?!
name: Tentacles of Death!

description: Continuing the all-new adventures set in the continuity of the new Fox Kids cartoon! Is Wolverine stalking the streets of Counter Earth's Manhattan? Maybe... maybe not! Meanwhile, Peter Parker returns from his meeting with this world's Reed Richards and Ben Grimm with a head full of questions. Are there an Aunt May and Mary Jane here, too? And if so, whose side are they on?

Its X-Men: ReLoad Wave 2! Rob Liefeld and Fabian Nicieza return to the title they made famousX-FORCE! Cable, Domino, Cannonball, Shatterstar, Warpath and all the rest return in this new series! New heroes, new villains, and big action... X-Force just the way you want it!
Metropolis has a brand new hero unlike any the city has ever seen! Meet the Minuteman...but does he have anything to do with the city's children turning into insects?
name: The Mack Minute

description: The chilling prophecy of the Minuteman comes to pass as children are turning to insects! Meanwhile, Superman finds himself battling the Anti-Angelica in both his world and theirs!
name: Mighty Bubbles

description: Take a walk down Memory Lane...or rather Santa Claus Lane, as Superman and Lois recount stories such as "The Secret of the Phantom Quarterback," "Crisis on Earth Mind," and "The Day the Earth Divided."
name: Bittersweet

description: Continuing the 3-part "Strange New Visitor!" Out of the raging storm that plagues Metropolis comes a new hero from another world, poised to take Superman's place in the DCU! Can Majestic truly fill the void left by the Man of Steel?
name: Strange New Visitor; Part 2

description: "Godfall" continues with Part 2 of 6! Kal-El's powers begin to emerge as he faces a new threat on Krypton. Plus, in the back-up by Greg Rucka (WONDER WOMAN, BATMAN: DEATH AND THE MAIDENS), Matt Clark & Nelson, the new head of the Metropolis Special Crimes Unit is introduced, while Superman is nowhere to be found in the city.
name: Godfall Part Two: Unravel

description: The penultimate chapter of the "Godfall" saga finds Kal-El pursued by the law and allied with former enemies! He's fighting for his life, but will it be worth it?
name: Godfall Part Five: Tempest

description: The debut of new team of acclaimed writer Greg Rucka, Matthew Clark & Nelson and cover artists Gene Ha! An old foe comes to Metropolis with murder ? and something much more sinister ? on his mind. Meanwhile, Clark's job troubles continue as he rides along with the Special Crimes Unit.
name: Battery: Part One

description: In part 2 of Battery, Superman deals with the outcome of his appearance in the part 1. Wonder Woman pays Lois a visit as Green Lantern John Stewart joins Superman in space looking for something and find something completely different. Lois prepares to go cover a war and Clark warns her about her safety. Fan Favorite Greg Rucka continues his run on the series as Mathew Clark lends the pencils.
name: Battery: Part Two

description: Reporting from Umec, Lois doesnt like the constraints the U.S. military has put on the press. Meanwhile, Superman battles a new and even more powerful Replikon as well as Lup, the femme fatale in charge of the SCU, who considers herself to be Clarks new boss!
name: Battery: Part Three

description: While saving some high-school hostages from a villain called Ruin, Superman gets a visit from the pesky pixie from the fifth dimension, Mr. Mxyzptlk. He warns big blue of an oncoming crisis, but Superman doesn't buy it. Then he returns Supes to fight Ruin.
name: Battery: Part Four

person_credits.name: Mike Kazaleh
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover
